            <title>[HBASE-3747] [replication] ReplicationSource should differanciate remote and local exceptions</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3747</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;From Jeff Whiting on the list:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m not sure...the key to everything was realizing picking up on RemoteException in &quot;Unable to replicate because org.apache.hadoop.ipc.RemoteException&quot; and realizing that it was on the replication cluster.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If it said something like &quot;Unable to replicate. Destination cluster threw an exception: org.apache.hadoop.ipc.RemoteException: java.io.IOException: java.lang.RuntimeException:&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Or something that makes it clear it is an exception on the remote or destination cluster would be helpful.  It is easy to scan over org.apache.hadoop.ipc.RemoteException and read it like &quot;org.ap...some-kind-of...exception.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
